        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): fail fast on missing local probe auth",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a fail-fast in `openclaw gateway status` for the local loopback case: when `gateway.auth.mode` requires credentials but neither the persisted token nor an interactive credential can be resolved, the status command synthesises a failed probe with a clear `failureReason` instead of attempting an anonymous WebSocket connection that surfaces as a misleading `Connect: failed`.\n\nExplicit `--url`/`--rpc-url` targets are intentionally exempt: a user pointing at a remote, forwarded, or open gateway should not be blocked by missing local-config credentials.\n\n## Details\n\n- `resolveAuthForTarget` resolves through the probe-surface helper. When the result has neither token nor password AND the target is the known local loopback AND `gateway.auth.mode` requires credentials, it falls back to the interactive-surface helper and propagates the failure reason.\n- The fail-fast is scoped to `surface === \"local\" && target.kind === \"localLoopback\"`. Targets with `kind === \"explicit\"` (i.e. `--url`/`--rpc-url`) skip the check.\n- Tests cover both the local fail-fast path and the explicit-target carve-out, and isolate ambient `gateway.auth.token` env in the probe-auth test to avoid cross-test contamination.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: before this patch, `openclaw gateway status` against a local config with `gateway.auth.mode: \"token\"` but an unresolvable token (e.g. `secrets.token.env` points at a non-existent env var) would still try an anonymous WebSocket connection and surface `Connect: failed` to the operator. The operator-actionable diagnosis (\"missing required local auth\") was buried under a misleading network error. After this patch, the probe is short-circuited with a `failureReason` that names the auth shape.\n\n- **Real environment tested**: deployed `openclaw` runtime built from this PR head on a local laptop checkout at `/tmp/wt-68280` (rebased onto `upstream/main` at `8e1b0e61b0`), run against an isolated test config at `/tmp/probe-test-68280/openclaw.json` so the live mac-mini gateway and its real auth are not touched. The test config sets `gateway.auth.mode: \"token\"` and `gateway.secrets.token.env` to an env var that is explicitly unset in the shell.\n\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  ```\n  unset OPENCLAW_PROBE_NONEXISTENT_TEST_VAR\n  OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/tmp/probe-test-68280/openclaw.json node dist/index.js gateway status --json | jq '.rpc | {ok, error, kind}'\n  OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/tmp/probe-test-68280/openclaw.json node dist/index.js gateway status --url ws://127.0.0.1:18999 --json | jq '{rpc: .rpc | {ok, error, kind}, probeUrl: .gateway.probeUrl}'\n  ```\n\n- **Evidence after fix**: Captured live from the patched `node dist/index.js` runtime built from this PR head. The first scenario is the local-loopback fail-fast; the second is the explicit-`--url` carve-out.\n\n  ```\n  $ node dist/index.js gateway status --json | jq '.rpc | {ok, error, kind}'\n  {\n    \"ok\": false,\n    \"error\": \"Missing gateway auth token.\",\n    \"kind\": null\n  }\n\n  $ node dist/index.js gateway status --url ws://127.0.0.1:18999 --json | jq '{rpc: .rpc | {ok, error, kind}, probeUrl: .gateway.probeUrl}'\n  {\n    \"rpc\": {\n      \"ok\": false,\n      \"error\": \"connect ECONNREFUSED 127.0.0.1:18999\",\n      \"kind\": \"connect\"\n    },\n    \"probeUrl\": \"ws://127.0.0.1:18999\"\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: in the local-loopback scenario, `rpc.kind` is `null` (no probe attempt was made) and `rpc.error` names the actionable auth diagnostic instead of a network error. In the explicit-URL scenario, `rpc.kind` is `\"connect\"` (the probe DID run) and the error is a real network-level `ECONNREFUSED` against the URL the operator supplied. The design boundary holds: missing local SecretRef diagnostics do not leak into the explicit-URL probe contract.\n\n- **What was not tested**: the explicit-URL daemon `--rpc-url` flag was not exercised end-to-end in this proof. The carve-out is structural (`target.kind !== \"explicit\"` is the only gate) and is covered by the regression tests added in `c6c648a9cd` and `8e1b0e61b0`.\n",
        "branch": "fix/loopback-local-probe-auth",
